            <i outputclass="Term"
               xtrf="_22.103-1"
               xtrc="d1297e15"
               class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Normal workweek</i>, as used in this subpart, means, generally, a workweek of 40 hours. Outside the United States and its outlying areas, a workweek longer than 40 hours is considered normal if-<ol id="d1271e16" class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <ol id="d1271e20" class="- topic/ol ">
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p " id="d1307e16">
                           <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> The workweek does not exceed the norm for the area, as determined by local custom, tradition, or law; and</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p " id="d1307e21">
                           <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> The hours worked in excess of 40 in the workweek are not compensated at a premium rate of pay.</p>
                     </li>
                  </ol>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </p>
